# ABC function

def condition_abc(x):
 if x>0 and x<=0.80:
   return "A"
 elif x>0.80 and x<=0.90:
   return "B"
 else:
   return 'C'

df_melted = abc_pivot_data.melt(id_vars=["Part No"], var_name="Month", value_name="Sales")

# Remove non-month columns (like total_sales)
df_melted = df_melted[df_melted["Month"] != "total_sales"]

# Convert "Month" column to datetime format for proper sorting
df_melted["Month"] = pd.to_datetime(df_melted["Month"], format="%Y/%m")

# Aggregate sales per month
monthly_sales = df_melted.groupby("Month")["Sales"].sum().reset_index()

# Plot the trend

sns.lineplot(data=monthly_sales, x="Month", y="Sales", marker="o", linewidth=2, color="b")

# Assuming df is your DataFrame
df_melted = abc_pivot_data.melt(id_vars=["Part No"], var_name="Month", value_name="Sales")

# Remove total_sales column
df_melted = df_melted[df_melted["Month"] != "total_sales"]

# Convert Month column to datetime format
df_melted["Month"] = pd.to_datetime(df_melted["Month"], format="%Y/%m")

# Extract Year and Month for grouping
df_melted["Year"] = df_melted["Month"].dt.year
df_melted["Month_Num"] = df_melted["Month"].dt.month

# Aggregate total sales per year-month
monthly_sales = df_melted.groupby(["Year", "Month_Num"])["Sales"].sum().reset_index()

# Calculate Coefficient of Varaince (CoV) for XYZ Classification

# Coefficient of variance is used for demand/sales uncertainty,, variability of products.
# It is calculated as (standard devaiation of item) divided by (average demand of item).

# Interpretation of CoV
# Low CoV: 
# Indicates low variability relative to the mean, meaning the product demand or sales is stable and predictable.
# High CoV: 
# Indicates high variability relative to the mean, meaning the product demand or sales is highly uncertain and unpredictable.

def xyz_classify_product(cov):
    """Apply an XYZ classification to each product based on 
    its coefficient of variation in order quantity.

    :param cov: Coefficient of variation in order quantity for SKU
    :return: XYZ inventory classification class
    """

    if cov <= 0.5:
        return 'X'
    elif cov > 0.5 and cov <= 1.0:
        return 'Y'
    else:
        return 'Z'

fsn_data_agg = FSN_data.groupby("Part No").agg(
    total_quantity=("Sold Qty", "sum"),      # Total consumption
    frequency=("Invoice Date", "count"),     # Number of transactions
    last_used=("Invoice Date", "max")        # Most recent transaction date
).reset_index()

# Compute recency (days since last transaction)
fsn_data_agg["last_used"] = pd.to_datetime(fsn_data_agg["last_used"])
FSN_data["Invoice Date"]= pd.to_datetime(FSN_data["Invoice Date"])
fsn_data_agg["recency"] = (FSN_data["Invoice Date"].max() - fsn_data_agg["last_used"]).dt.days

# Compute percentile-based thresholds
q_high = fsn_data_agg["total_quantity"].quantile(0.70)
q_low = fsn_data_agg["total_quantity"].quantile(0.30)

f_high = fsn_data_agg["frequency"].quantile(0.70)
f_low = fsn_data_agg["frequency"].quantile(0.30)

r_high = fsn_data_agg["recency"].quantile(0.70)
r_low = fsn_data_agg["recency"].quantile(0.30)
In [35]:
# Asign FSN category
In [36]:
# Function to classify FSN
def classify_fsn(row):
    if row["total_quantity"] >= q_high and row["frequency"] >= f_high:
        return "F"  # Fast-moving
    elif row["total_quantity"] <= q_low and row["frequency"] <= f_low and row["recency"] >= r_high:
        return "N"  # Non-moving
    else:
        return "S"  # Slow-moving"

fsn_data_agg["FSN_Category"] = fsn_data_agg.apply(classify_fsn, axis=1)

# Compute summary
abc_xyz_fsn_summary = final_category_data.groupby("ABC_XYZ_FSN").agg(
    total_revenue=("total_sales", "sum"),
    total_quantity=("total_quantity", "sum")
).reset_index()

# Plot
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

# Bar plot for total revenue
sns.barplot(x="ABC_XYZ_FSN", y="total_revenue", data=abc_xyz_fsn_summary, ax=ax1, color="blue", alpha=0.6)
ax1.set_ylabel("Total Revenue", color="blue")
ax1.tick_params(axis="y", labelcolor="blue")

# Create second y-axis for total quantity
ax2 = ax1.twinx()
sns.lineplot(x="ABC_XYZ_FSN", y="total_quantity", data=abc_xyz_fsn_summary, ax=ax2, color="red", marker="o")
ax2.set_ylabel("Total Quantity", color="red")
ax2.tick_params(axis="y", labelcolor="red")

# Titles and labels
plt.title("Total Revenue & Quantity by ABC_XYZ_FSN Category")
plt.xlabel("ABC_XYZ_FSN Category")

# Show plot
plt.show()
